                <h2>Research</h2>
                <p>One of the major characteristics of effective design is a clear user interface. All the elements need to be well-balanced and placed in the harmony. This could be achieved by the good use of ratios.
The golden ratio is a mathematical proportion between the elements of different sizes which is thought to be the most aes- thetically pleasing for human eyes. The golden ratio equals 1:1.618
Using the golden ratio in web design is mostly using the golden rectangle to determine how to place elements on the website.
I’ve applied the golden ratio to the product page to emphasize on the product image as well as the call to action which are both strategically placed to catch the eye.</p>
